         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">[ ¶ Melbourne,11 August 1886 ¶  ¶ 're £100 Grant'. The sum of £100 has been raised by the Victorian Branch of the Royal Geographical Society of Australasia to aid the New South Wales Branch in paying ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.08.11<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Strickland</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.853/2 letter register, no. 1070, Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (NSW Branch) papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of NSW, Sydney.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">Transcribed 11.5.90. Corrected 21.4.93, 20.5.93. To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. Item is a register entry only.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">M's letter is also recorded as having been received by the Society on 11 August 1886. It was possibly a telegram sent the same day.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">I therefore infer that the Melbourne, 11 August 1886 is part of the text in the register</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">; is that so</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">?</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>If not the case then "also recorded" is a bit odd.</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I would have expected Strickland to have used "telegram" rather than letter in "</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">I have been in bed during the last week, for five days, during that time I received your second<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                          style="color: #C00000; background-color: #FFFF00; ">very kind letter of the 11th</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>telling me of your kind and successful efforts to get together £100 to send to us."</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I would also have expected the register to include a record of the letter telling Strickland "</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">On the very day on which I received your letter</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">announcing that you had secured £1000 in the Estimates for your branch of the Society, I was taken ill</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">"</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The language of 86-08-15 could be read as meaning both letters were written on 11 August, bhut it is ambiguous "could mean second letter about grants, written on 11</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">th</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">"</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                  </p>
               </note>[<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">Melbourne,11 August 1886</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'re £100 Grant'. The sum of £100 has been raised by the Victorian Branch of the Royal Geographical Society of Australasia to aid the New South Wales Branch in paying its liabilities.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See E. Strickland to M, 15 August 1886, in which he refers to M's 'very kind letter of the 11th'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
